text.tspan: Select an album to add to.

flowRoot.flowPara: Organiser view shows the photo stream ordered by recency. Clicking a photo always selects it.
Albums are listed in order of creation, and can be searched.
View changes when new album is selected. Thumbnails show photos that will be added to the album, to provide a preview of what it will look like.
Order is used for display, export and slideshows. Thumbnails can be dragged to rearrange when manual ordering is set?
Add button becomes sensitive once an album has been selected.
Create button becomes sensitive once an album name has been entered.
Acting on multiple albums isn't going to be typical, so there's no selection mode here. Context menus are used instead.
FIXME: no way to see which albums a photo is already in.
